Community Board 9 has no protected path bike lanes.

Community Board 9, which includes West Harlem, is the only Manhattan community board (outlined in grey) without bike lanes classified as “protected path” by the NYC Department of Transportation.

Community Board 9

Each blue line represents an existing protected path bike lane.

Manhattan

“Protected path” lanes have physical separation from motorized vehicle traffic by a parking lane or other barrier.

Note: Bike lanes inside parks are classified as “greenways” and are not shown. Source: NYC Open Data. Last updated June 6, 2023.

Graphic by Adina Cazacu-De Luca
